'''VMmark''' is a freeware [[virtual machine]] [[Benchmark (computing)|benchmark]] software suite from [[VMware]], Inc., a division of [[EMC Corporation]]. The suite measures the performance of virtualized servers while running under load on a set of physical hardware. VMmark was developed by VMware in conjunction with the [[Standard Performance Evaluation Corporation]], a non-profit developer of performance benchmarks for the computer industry.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.vmware.com/products/vmmark/faq.html |title=VMmark FAQs: Will VMmark be an industry standard? If so, what is VMware doing towards this goal? |publisher=VMware, Inc. |accessdate=2007-10-16}}</ref>
